#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
CaddyLatch — on-demand Caddy edge access controller.

Controls a WireGuard tunnel and Caddy's geo/IP filtering to provide
time-boxed, scoped remote access through a Caddy reverse proxy edge.

Default state: locked. WireGuard is down, Caddy blocks all traffic.
When enabled: WireGuard comes up, Caddy allows traffic from specified
countries and IPs only, with a self-destruct timer.

Architecture:
  - Single agent on the edge VPS (this script)
  - Status endpoint on a trusted network (e.g., Tailscale)
  - Home-side WireGuard stays always-on; this agent is the sole gatekeeper
  - Web app (separate) talks to the status endpoint to toggle state

Designed for:
  - Caddy with caddy-maxmind-geolocation plugin
  - WireGuard managed by wg-quick systemd units
  - MaxMind GeoLite2-Country database
"""

